code:
```python
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='open', kde=True, color='blue', bins=20)
    plt.axvline(data['open'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['open'].median():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of opening prices?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Opening Prices")
    plt.ylabel("Frequency")
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='open', data=data, label='Opening Price', color='blue')
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='close', data=data, label='Closing Price', color='red')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between opening and closing prices?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Price')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.countplot(x='signal', data=data, palette='pastel')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of trading signals?', wrap=True)
    ax.set_xlabel('Trading Signals')
    ax.set_ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend(title='Trading Signals', loc='upper right', labels=data['signal'].unique())
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
